{"@context": "http://schema.org", "@type": "Movie", "url": "/title/tt0092965/", "name": "Empire of the Sun", "image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMmQwNzczZDItNmI0OS00MjRmLTliYWItZWIyMjk1MTU4ZTQ4L2ltYWdlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTAyODkwOQ@@._V1_.jpg", "genre": ["Action", "Drama", "History", "War"], "contentRating": "PG", "actor": [{"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0000288/", "name": "Christian Bale"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0000518/", "name": "John Malkovich"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0001669/", "name": "Miranda Richardson"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0369814/", "name": "Nigel Havers"}], "director": {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0000229/", "name": "Steven Spielberg"}, "creator": [{"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0001779/", "name": "Tom Stoppard"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0050618/", "name": "J.G. Ballard"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0583675/", "name": "Menno Meyjes"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0009119/"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0002663/"}], "description": "Empire of the Sun is a movie starring Christian Bale, John Malkovich, and Miranda Richardson. A young English boy struggles to survive under Japanese occupation of China during World War II.", "datePublished": "1987-12-25", "keywords": "battle,murder,chase,explosion,student", "aggregateRating": {"@type": "AggregateRating", "ratingCount": 116695, "bestRating": "10.0", "worstRating": "1.0", "ratingValue": "7.7"}, "review": {"@type": "Review", "itemReviewed": {"@type": "CreativeWork", "url": "/title/tt0092965/"}, "author": {"@type": "Person", "name": "JMichaelAtchue"}, "dateCreated": "2019-11-21", "inLanguage": "English", "name": "An Underrated Classic", "reviewBody": "In 1987 Steven Spielberg's \"Empire of the Sun\" opened to mixed reviews and disappointing box office returns. But the film's reputation has grown with time, and it's now rightfully considered an underrated Spielberg classic. \"Empire of the Sun\" tells the true story of Jim Ballard, an English boy who's separated from his parents in China during World War II. Featuring an excellent performance from the young Christian Bale, \"Empire of the Sun\" is an emotional and visually striking drama about loss, family, and the horror of war. Spielberg also uses Ballard's story to address thought-provoking questions about social privilege, militarism, and the lengths that humans will go to in order to survive. Spielberg doesn't provide easy answers to these questions, making this one of his more mature and contemplative works.\n\nHaving seen \"Empire of the Sun\" multiple times, I've grown to deeply appreciate it as both a sweeping historical epic and a powerful tale of a traumatic childhood. The movie isn't perfect - at two and a half hours it's too long. The second act in particular drags and this causes the movie to lose much of its dramatic momentum halfway through. But despite its length \"Empire of the Sun\" does more than enough to maintain your interest with compelling performances, amazing visuals, and of course John Williams' award winning score. 8/10.", "reviewRating": {"@type": "Rating", "worstRating": "1", "bestRating": "10", "ratingValue": "8"}}, "duration": "PT2H33M", "trailer": {"@type": "VideoObject", "name": "Empire of the Sun", "embedUrl": "/video/imdb/vi497352985", "thumbnail": {"@type": "ImageObject", "contentUrl": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNWE2YzliMmQtMzAyOS00ZTIzLWE2YjItNzU1NzNjZDRlNGQ3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzU1NzE3NTg@._V1_.jpg"}, "thumbnailUrl": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNWE2YzliMmQtMzAyOS00ZTIzLWE2YjItNzU1NzNjZDRlNGQ3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzU1NzE3NTg@._V1_.jpg", "description": "Home Video Trailer from Warner Home Video", "uploadDate": "2008-04-11T14:00:13Z"}, "cast_and_character": [{"actor": {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0000288/?ref_=tt_cl_t1", "name": "Christian Bale"}, "character_and_episodes": [{"url": "/title/tt0092965/characters/nm0000288?ref_=tt_cl_t1", "name